body:
Ashes (Jorah x Daenerys)

I wanted to do something different but I’m not at home and it’s @asoiafrarepairs week round 2, so there’s a little drabble I wrote. 

WARNING: evil!Daenerys. Don’t like, don’t read. 


“Khaleesi,” Jorah whispered, not daring to speak louder, his usually low voice sounding even deeper now that he was doing everything in his power for not being heard by anyone but the young girl in front of him. Who wasn’t young anymore. He looked at her, saw her turning from the scared girl he met on the day of her wedding into a strong woman. And now she was standing in front of the Iron Throne.


The smile on her lips, despite everything, was malicious and threatening. Jorah didn’t notice it or pretended he didn’t. He couldn’t say, he pretended not to notice a lot of things, with the passing of years.


“Jorah,” She said, not Ser before his name, and maybe he was a fool in believing that she would ever look at him like she looked at the throne at her backs, but he decided he didn’t care either.

Lannister was right, she was going to rule on a Kingdom made of ashes as her ancestors did. But Jorah didn’t care, he couldn’t. Because he was the only person Daenerys Targaryen still trusted, and he could pretend that was enough. She spoke again: “Bring the traitors to the Dragon Pit.”


Jorah nodded, and before he left the room she stepped down the Throne, placing a chaste kiss against the man’s lips. Jorah looked at how her silver hair looked like flames under the torches that were lighting the Throne Room. His Queen was beautiful, he thought.

He saw her smiling again that wicked smile while she looked at the remains of Jon Snow and Tyrion Lannister’s bodies in the golden sand of the Dragon Pit, and Jorah hated himself. But he said nothing. And the only thing he said, that night, was Daenerys’s name, while his fingers were digging in the soft flesh of her waist, and she screamed his name.


She was the Queen of Ashes, but she was his, and Jorah couldn’t bring himself to see who she really was.
